  <bioghist id="aspace_5769cb48bb7ffb9af4e59000990d1577">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Professor emeritus in the Division of Nutritional Sciences, Cornell University.</p><p>  Morrison served in the Royal Canadian Air Force from 1943-1946 and received a B.A. form the University of Alberta, a master's degree in food and nutrition from Washington State University, and a PhD in biochemistry/nutrition from the University of Wisconsin.</p><p> Morrison taught from 1960-1988 and her teaching and research focused on protein and amino acid nutrition. At Cornell she developed an undergraduate honors seminar, directed a multidisciplinary research action program in East Harlem, New York (1969-1976) and chaired the Northeast Regional Technical Committee, which coordinated the research work of faculty in ten universities.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_38961b02bdf115babb87648d33f8232f">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Correspondence, publications, reports and subject files realted to Morrison's work as a professor in the Division of Nutritional Sciences (1960-1988) and with the Nutrition Education Program in East Harlem, the University Animal Welfare Committee (UAWC) and faculty retirement issues.</p>  </scopecontent>
